 carrying amount of an asset may not be recoverable the calculation of the value in use is based on the definition of discounted future cash flows the projected cash flows are prepared taking into account i projections of the price of liquids and purchase costs of natural gas associated with our liquids production and commercialization segment including the impact of the gas charge resolutions and other services segment ii estimates relating to the timing type and amount of the tariff increase and the recognition of cost adjustments for the natural gas transportation segment iii projections of future costs to be incurred and iv the use of certain macroeconomic variables such as interest rates inflation changes in the exchange rate in accordance with the budget for the upcoming fiscal year approved by the board of directors the discount rate is our weighted average cost of capital  wacc  we recorded no impairment losses of components of property plant and equipment as of december   and  due to the uncertainties surrounding the tariff renegotiation process as described in note a to our financial statements estimates of future tariff adjustments are highly uncertain and there is a substantial risk that these estimates could prove to be materially different from actual future tariffs for this reason we performed probabilityweighted analysis as to the cash flow assumptions considered in performing an impairment test of our natural gas transportation business segment as of the end of each year we considered two different scenarios · scenario  we are able to reach an agreement with the government regarding a tariff increase scenario  and · scenario  we are unable to reach an agreement with the government resulting in no tariff increase during the remaining term of our license including the entire extension period scenario  as of december   we assigned a probability of occurrence of  to scenario  and a probability of occurrence of  to scenario   transportadora de gas 