ncial assets as our debt is almost  us dollar denominated in the short term the most significant factors generally affecting our cash flow from operating activities are i fluctuations in international prices for lpg products ii fluctuations in production levels and demand for our products and services iii changes in regulations such as taxes taxes on exports tariff for our regulated business segment and price controls and iv fluctuations in exchange rates  transportadora de gas del sur sa notes to the consolidated financial statements as of december   and comparative information stated in thousands of pesos as described in note  unless otherwise stated within the framework of the  transitional agreement in the fiscal years  and  we received two tariff increases these increases were not enough to offset the significant increases in costs recorded over the last years in spite of our continuous efforts to reduce them although this situation has resulted in an annual operating loss in the last two years the tariff increases were important to achieve the aim of partially improving the economic situation of this business segment until we arrive at an understanding with the government with respect to the integral renegotiation agreement both tariff increases were authorized by resolutions no i and no i issued by enargas and include the following increases respectively · a stepped increase of  as from april    accumulated since june   and  accumulated since august   · as from may   a transitional increase of  in the price of the natural gas transportation service and  in the cau in march  the enargas granted us a transitional increase of  in natural gas transportation tariffs and the cau effective april   the purpose of the increase is to cover costs and investments associated with the regular provision of the public service of natural gas transportation until the integral renegotiation agreements is finalized  pursuant to resolution no  we must also execute the investment 